## 5. Compatibility & Setup Guide

- Best Blade Matches
    - Outer Carbon: Only recommended for highly advanced players; the combined stiffness can make the setup feel too rigid.
    - Inner Carbon: Highly recommended. An ALC or ZLC inner blade provides the necessary flex to dwell the ball while supporting the hard sponge.
    - All-Wood: Excellent pairing for spin development and maximum dwell time (e.g., 7-ply wood).
    - Mismatch Cases: Soft 5-ply beginner blades (too slow to activate the sponge) or excessively stiff composite blades (zero dwell time).

- Forehand vs. Backhand Recommendation
    - Forehand: Ideal. The hard sponge caters perfectly to the natural power and larger swing of a forehand stroke.
    - Backhand: Only for elite players with extremely fast, compact backhand snaps. For most, it will feel too hard.

